=head1 DESCRIPTION

Information about when an on-call rotation is in effect and how long
the rotation period lasts.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 DailySettings => ArrayRef[L<Paws::SSMContacts::HandOffTime>]

Information about on-call rotations that recur daily.


=head2 MonthlySettings => ArrayRef[L<Paws::SSMContacts::MonthlySetting>]

Information about on-call rotations that recur monthly.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> NumberOfOnCalls => Int

The number of contacts, or shift team members designated to be on call
concurrently during a shift. For example, in an on-call schedule
containing ten contacts, a value of C<2> designates that two of them
are on call at any given time.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> RecurrenceMultiplier => Int

The number of days, weeks, or months a single rotation lasts.


=head2 ShiftCoverages => L<Paws::SSMContacts::ShiftCoveragesMap>

Information about the days of the week included in on-call rotation
coverage.


=head2 WeeklySettings => ArrayRef[L<Paws::SSMContacts::WeeklySetting>]

Information about on-call rotations that recur weekly.



